When he was a teenager, Dan was in a building when magnesium flares ignited.
Dan Ariely: I spent almost three years in the hospital.
The big thing that I used to have debates with the nurses about was whether we should take the bandages off slowly or quickly.
Charles Duhigg: Once he recovered, Dan went on to study psychology and things like how we make choices when we’re in pain or we’re confronting pain.
One of the irrational behaviors that Dan spent a lot of time looking at is procrastination.